Reference: https://docs.python.org/3/library/pdb.html

pdb is Pythonâ€™s built-in interactive source code debugger. It allows you to pause your program, inspect variables, step through code line by line, and troubleshoot issues.

Why use pdb?
    Step through code line by line
    Set breakpoints
    Inspect variable values during execution
    Change variable values on the fly (if needed)
    Continue execution or jump to specific lines

Commands

l	List source code around the current line
n	Next line
s	Step into function
c	Continue execution
b	Set breakpoint
p	Print a variable
q	Quit debugging